cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the vulnerability of anti-spoofing methods based on deep learning against adversarial perturbations in the context of face authentication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the security aspect of the face authentication system, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes a method to craft robust physical domain adversarial images, which involves deep learning techniques, making it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper uses a database and mobile phone camera to validate the proposed attack, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed attack, which involves the evaluation of the performance of the face authentication system, making it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
